    <body>
      <section eId="sec_146_G">
        <num>146-G</num>
        <heading>Retail sale</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_146_G__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>display such phosphorus-containing specialty fertilizer separately\nfrom non-phosphorus specialty fertilizer; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_146_G__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>post in the location where phosphorus-containing specialty\nfertilizer is displayed a clearly visible sign which is at least eight\nand one-half inches by eleven inches in size and states that:\n  "Phosphorus runoff poses a threat to water quality. Therefore, under\nNew York law, phosphorus-containing fertilizer may only be applied to\nlawn or non-agricultural turf when:\n</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="sec_146_G__subsec_b__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A soil test indicates that additional phosphorus is needed for\ngrowth of that lawn or non-agricultural turf; or\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_146_G__subsec_b__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The fertilizer is used for newly established lawn or\nnon-agricultural turf during the first growing season."\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
      </section>
